Hi,

I have created the python script to read tdms file using nptdms library . I have to call this script from java . I am using jython to run python script from java. When I am calling the script it is giving exception that "Cannot import nptdms module". I am using "from nptdms import TdmsFile" line in the script . Could you please help me. 

Below is code that I am using in java code to call the script.

    ScriptEngineManager scriptingEngineManager=new ScriptEngineManager();
    ScriptEngine scriptEngine=scriptingEngineManager.getEngineByName("python");
    System.out.print("system engine "+scriptEngine);
    scriptEngine.eval(new BufferedReader(new FileReader("demo.py")));

I try to use query_serializer in `@swagger_auto_schema` to document my get method. The structure of QuerySerializer is show up on generated schema page , but with no label.

```python
from drf_yasg.utils import swagger_auto_schema
from rest_framework import serializers
from rest_framework.views import APIView


class QuerySerializer(serializers.Serializer):
    name_in_query = serializers.CharField(required=True, label="name of query serializer")


class ResponseSerializer(serializers.Serializer):
    name_in_response = serializers.CharField(label='name of response serializer')


class TestView(APIView):
    @swagger_auto_schema(
        query_serializer=QuerySerializer,  # no label show up
        responses={200: ResponseSerializer}
    )
    def get(self, request):
        pass
```

But i change to use `manual_parameters=[test_param]` of `@swagger_auto_schema`, the description show up correctly on the generated schema page.
```python
test_param = openapi.Parameter('test', openapi.IN_QUERY, description="test manual param", type=openapi.TYPE_STRING)

class TestView(APIView):
    @swagger_auto_schema(
        manual_parameters=[test_param],  # label show up
        responses={200: ResponseSerializer}
    )
    def get(self, request):
        pass
```


It will be nice to support label of serializer used as query_serializer of `@swagger_auto_schema`, instead of writing lots of `openapi.Parameter`

